cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on edge computing and proposes a new computing paradigm, edge cognitive computing, which applies cognitive computing at the edge of the network. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of cognitive computing in edge computing and proposes a dynamic service migration mechanism based on behavioral cognition of a mobile user. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a new computing paradigm that aims to provide elastic cognitive computing services to achieve a higher energy efficiency and a higher Quality of Experience (QoE) compared to edge computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a mechanism for dynamic service migration in edge cognitive computing, which involves controlling the migration of services based on the behavioral cognition of a mobile user. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of cognitive computing in edge computing, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms to provide cognition of users and network environmental information.
